 361              	arm_rfft_fast_f32:
 362              	.LVL50:
 363              	.LFB355:
 174:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c **** 
 175:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c **** /**
 176:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c **** * @ingroup groupTransforms
 177:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c **** */
 178:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c **** 
 179:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c **** /**
 180:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * @defgroup RealFFT Real FFT Functions
 181:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  *
 182:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 183:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The CMSIS DSP library includes specialized algorithms for computing the
 184:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * FFT of real data sequences.  The FFT is defined over complex data but
 185:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * in many applications the input is real.  Real FFT algorithms take advantage
 186:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * of the symmetry properties of the FFT and have a speed advantage over complex
 187:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * algorithms of the same length.
 188:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 189:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The Fast RFFT algorith relays on the mixed radix CFFT that save processor usage.
 190:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 191:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The real length N forward FFT of a sequence is computed using the steps shown below.
 192:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 193:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \image html RFFT.gif "Real Fast Fourier Transform"
 194:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 195:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The real sequence is initially treated as if it were complex to perform a CFFT.
 196:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * Later, a processing stage reshapes the data to obtain half of the frequency spectrum
 197:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * in complex format. Except the first complex number that contains the two real numbers
 198:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * X[0] and X[N/2] all the data is complex. In other words, the first complex sample
 199:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * contains two real values packed.
 200:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 201:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The input for the inverse RFFT should keep the same format as the output of the
 202:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * forward RFFT. A first processing stage pre-process the data to later perform an
 203:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * inverse CFFT.
 204:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 205:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \image html RIFFT.gif "Real Inverse Fast Fourier Transform"
 206:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 207:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The algorithms for floating-point, Q15, and Q31 data are slightly different
 208:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * and we describe each algorithm in turn.
 209:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par Floating-point
 210:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The main functions are arm_rfft_fast_f32() and arm_rfft_fast_init_f32().
 211:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The older functions arm_rfft_f32() and arm_rfft_init_f32() have been
 212:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * deprecated but are still documented.
 213:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 214:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The FFT of a real N-point sequence has even symmetry in the frequency
 215:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * domain. The second half of the data equals the conjugate of the first
 216:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * half flipped in frequency. Looking at the data, we see that we can
 217:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * uniquely represent the FFT using only N/2 complex numbers. These are
ARM GAS  /var/folders/6_/psd2b8g56p7696hhrr4ztjs00000gn/T//ccAXDgRX.s 			page 13


 218:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * packed into the output array in alternating real and imaginary
 219:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * components:
 220:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 221:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * X = { real[0], imag[0], real[1], imag[1], real[2], imag[2] ...
 222:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * real[(N/2)-1], imag[(N/2)-1 }
 223:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 224:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * It happens that the first complex number (real[0], imag[0]) is actually
 225:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * all real. real[0] represents the DC offset, and imag[0] should be 0.
 226:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * (real[1], imag[1]) is the fundamental frequency, (real[2], imag[2]) is
 227:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * the first harmonic and so on.
 228:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 229:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The real FFT functions pack the frequency domain data in this fashion.
 230:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The forward transform outputs the data in this form and the inverse
 231:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * transform expects input data in this form. The function always performs
 232:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * the needed bitreversal so that the input and output data is always in
 233:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * normal order. The functions support lengths of [32, 64, 128, ..., 4096]
 234:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * samples.
 235:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par Q15 and Q31
 236:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The real algorithms are defined in a similar manner and utilize N/2 complex
 237:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * transforms behind the scenes.
 238:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 239:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The complex transforms used internally include scaling to prevent fixed-point
 240:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * overflows.  The overall scaling equals 1/(fftLen/2).
 241:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 242:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * A separate instance structure must be defined for each transform used but
 243:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * twiddle factor and bit reversal tables can be reused.
 244:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 245:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * There is also an associated initialization function for each data type.
 246:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The initialization function performs the following operations:
 247:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * - Sets the values of the internal structure fields.
 248:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * - Initializes twiddle factor table and bit reversal table pointers.
 249:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * - Initializes the internal complex FFT data structure.
 250:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * \par
 251:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * Use of the initialization function is optional.
 252:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * However, if the initialization function is used, then the instance structure
 253:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * cannot be placed into a const data section. To place an instance structure
 254:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * into a const data section, the instance structure should be manually
 255:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * initialized as follows:
 256:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <pre>
 257:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  *arm_rfft_instance_q31 S = {fftLenReal, fftLenBy2, ifftFlagR, bitReverseFlagR, twidCoefRModifier, 
 258:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  *arm_rfft_instance_q15 S = {fftLenReal, fftLenBy2, ifftFlagR, bitReverseFlagR, twidCoefRModifier, 
 259:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * </pre>
 260:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * where <code>fftLenReal</code> is the length of the real transform;
 261:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>fftLenBy2</code> length of  the internal complex transform.
 262:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>ifftFlagR</code> Selects forward (=0) or inverse (=1) transform.
 263:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>bitReverseFlagR</code> Selects bit reversed output (=0) or normal order
 264:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * output (=1).
 265:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>twidCoefRModifier</code> stride modifier for the twiddle factor table.
 266:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * The value is based on the FFT length;
 267:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>pTwiddleAReal</code>points to the A array of twiddle coefficients;
 268:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>pTwiddleBReal</code>points to the B array of twiddle coefficients;
 269:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * <code>pCfft</code> points to the CFFT Instance structure. The CFFT structure
 270:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * must also be initialized.  Refer to arm_cfft_radix4_f32() for details regarding
 271:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  * static initialization of the complex FFT instance structure.
 272:../libDaisy/Drivers/CMSIS/DSP/Source/TransformFunctions/arm_rfft_fast_f32.c ****  */
